            <div type="translation">
            <p>Cassandra.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Transcription from photo, consistent with Richter (1956 [1920]). Richter notes that
                    "To judge by the renderings of the drapery and of the features, the period of
                    the gem should be around 400-380 B.C., the time of the Nike Balustrade and the
                    Epidauros sculptures. The form of the ring conforms with this dating." The
                    inscription is written in reverse, indicating that the ring was used as a seal. </p></div>
            

